The 2022 Gordon Research Conference (GRC) on Flow and Transport in Permeable Media was held from July 18-22, 2022 in Les Diablerets, Switzerland. This biennial GRC has become the premier venue for researchers from academia, national labs, and industry to share their latest ideas and exciting research findings related to flow and transport in permeable media. The conference  highlighted theoretical, experimental, and field research aimed at understanding fundamental interactions between fluids, chemical elements, minerals and materials, energy and life in porous and fractured media, and discuss their consequences across scales and disciplines. The conference had sessions on:

Dynamics of Carbon Dioxide in the Subsurface; I
mpact of Fluid and Solid Deformation on Transport and Mixing; 
Controls of Subsurface Flow and Transport on Earth's Hydrological and Geochemical Cycles; 
Pore Scale Physics of Multiphase and Complex Flows; 
Biofilms and Bacteria; 
Coupled Flow and Transport in Ice and Planetary Systems; 
Non-Invasive Methods and Data Assimilation Strategies for Monitoring Subsurface Processes; 
Fractures, Hydromechanics and Seismicity; 
Soil Processes from Micro to Continental Scales.


Our research community emerged strong from the COVID hiatus and with 166 participants that conference had its largest attendance in history. A new generation of young researchers came out in force and more than half of the participants were graduate students and postdocs. This gave the conference a tremendous energy with lots of opportunities for interaction between junior and senior researchers and animated discussions in the poster hall until late into the night. The conference also broke new ground in gender equality with largest number of female speakers and participants in conference history. 

